summaries.short: Season Three Premiere. Will, Mac and the newsroom err on the side of caution in reporting a breaking story in Boston.
summaries.full: Season Three Premiere. Will, Mac and the News Night team decide to err on the side of caution in reporting a major breaking story; Neal is contacted by an anonymous source in possession of stolen government documents; Sloan looks to solve a takeover puzzle; Maggie is forced to pinch-hit for Elliot in the aftermath of the Boston Marathon bombings.

summaries.short: Aaron Sorkin and the stellar cast of 'The Newsroom' bid farewell to the acclaimed HBO drama series.
summaries.full: Aaron Sorkin and the stellar cast of 'The Newsroom' bid farewell to the acclaimed HBO drama series.

summaries.short: Will tries to protect Neal; Reese's half-siblings look to cash in on a hostile takeover gambit.
summaries.full: With Rebecca again tasked with defending ACN in a possible lawsuit, Will tries to protect Neal from the fallout over the DOD leak. Charlie and Leona enter the fray of a hostile-takeover gambit. Sloan fears Don may be guilty of cashing in on insider information; Maggie ponders the ethics of eavesdropping; Hallie pays a price for a late-night tweet.

summaries.short: Season Two Finale. Will and Charlie await an executive decision on the newsroom's fate as the 2012 election winds down.
summaries.full: Season Two Finale. As Election Night 2012 winds down, Will and Charlie await a decision from Reese that may impact their future at ACN, and that of the entire senior staff. Sloan learns the identity of the anonymous winning bidder for her book; Don discusses a countersuit against Dantana with Rebecca; Will has a revelation while Charlie shares his.

summaries.short: Will gets a surprise at the Correspondents' Dinner; Sloan and Don try to keep their relationship a secret.
summaries.full: Leona and Reece look to raise cash in order to salvage ACN and thwart Blair and Randy. Will gets a surprise at the White House Correspondents' Dinner, while Charlie trades visions with ACN suitor Lucas Pruit. Maggie's EPA scoop makes it to News Night. Sloan and Don try to keep their relationship a secret from the new HR veep.

summaries.short: News Night goes forward with its election-night coverage in what might be its last broadcast with Will and Mac.
summaries.full: News Night goes forward with its 2012 election-night coverage, with Will in the unlikely role of Director of Morale. Sloan is perturbed that her book was auctioned off with a forged signature, while Mac tasks Neal to fix a faulty Wikipedia page. Jim weighs the cons of retracting a call he made too soon. The team deliberates over a story that might impact a tight Senate race.

summaries.short: Will faces a contempt charge; Sloan and Mac try to prevent ACN from falling into Lucas's hands.
summaries.full: Facing a court subpoena and possible incarceration for contempt, Will stands firm in his refusal to reveal the source of the stolen DOD documents. As Charlie's distain for Lucas reaches a fever pitch, Sloan and Mac scramble to find a more acceptable, 11th-hour buyer for ACN. Jim's relationship with Hallie is put to the test by her new job at Carnivore, a start-up website.

summaries.short: Rebecca pieces together the staff's fateful decision to air Dantana's special report on Operation Genoa.
summaries.full: Through depositions with the newsroom staff, Rebecca pieces together the events that led to ACN's fateful decision to go forward with Dantana's special report on Operation Genoa--as well as the post-air revelations that undermined its credibility. The repercussions threaten to ruin News Night while eclipsing breaking news during another 9/11 anniversary.
